Program name: Teaching English as a Second Language

EnglishScore: Applicants whose native language is not English must demonstrate English proficiency in one of the following ways before they can be admitted to a graduate program.
For applicants whose native language is not English, proof of English proficiency is required.
In addition to the requirements listed above, international applicants must meet the minimum English proficiency requirements for graduate students at Kansas State University.
Applicants whose native language is not English must demonstrate English proficiency. Minimum scores are: TOEFL iBT 79, IELTS 6.5, PTE 58, or Duolingo 110.
